{| class="wikitable" |- | style="background:lightblue" align="left" width="650px" | [[Image:Flag of the United Nations.svg|300x45px]]'''[[Security Council]]''' | style="background:lightblue" align="center" width="120px" | ''Founded 1945'' |- | style="background:lightgrey" | '''Aspect''' | style="background:lightgrey" align="center" width="120px" | '''Supranational Element''' |- |The members of the United Nations agree that in carrying out its duties in maintaining peace and security, the Security Council Acts on their behalf.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter V, Article 24 | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 2 |- |The members of the United Nations agree to accept and carry out the decisions of the Security Council. Thus Security Council resolutions are binding on involved member states, or even on all member states.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter V, Article 25 | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 2 |- |The Security Council may compel the members states to apply measures decided upon to give effect to its decisions, such as diplomatic or economic sanctions.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter VII, Article 41 | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 2 |- |The Security Council may take action through the use of military force to enforce its decisions and maintain or restore international peace and security. This provision has been used somewhat infrequently – the [[Korean War]] (1950), intervention in the [[Congo Crisis]](1961), the First Gulf Conflict (1991) <ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter VII, Article 42 | publisher = | year = 1945 | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 2 |- |The Security Council may enforce the decisions of the International Court of Justice, although this provision has never been used.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter XIV, Article 94, Paragraph 1 | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 2 |- |The Security Council may create subsidiary organs to assist in carrying out its functions. Since the decisions of the Security Council are binding, the effect is that such subsidiary organs can add new ways for the Council to exercise its obligations. The most prominent examples of this were the creation of the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia and the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =United Nations Charter | work = [[United Nations Charter]], Chapter VI, Article 29 | publisher = | date = | url = https://www.un.org/aboutun/charter | format = | doi = | accessdate = }}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 3 |- |The Statute of the International Criminal Court confers upon the Security Council an ability to refer situations of war crimes, crimes against humanity, or genocide in states not party to the Statute to the ICC for investigation and prosecution.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court | work = [[Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court]], Article 13 | publisher = | date = | url = http://www.icc-cpi.int/library/about/officialjournal/Rome_Statute_120704-EN.pdf | format = | doi = | accessdate = |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050510175923/http://www.icc-cpi.int/library/about/officialjournal/Rome_Statute_120704-EN.pdf|archivedate=2005-05-10}}</ref> |align="center" width="120px" | 3 |}
