The '''World Archery Rankings''' is a ranking system developed by the [[World Archery Federation]] for [[Modern competitive archery|international competitive archery]]. It is calculated using a points system and published following major [[World Archery Federation|World Archery]] tournaments.
The ranking system was first developed in 2001, and calculation method updated in 2010. At present, rankings are maintained for: * '''[[Recurve bow|Recurve archery]]''': ''Men's Individual, Women's Individual, Men's Team, Women's Team, Mixed Team'' * '''[[Compound bow|Compound archery]]''': ''Men's Individual, Women's Individual, Men's Team, Women's Team, Mixed Team'' * '''Para-archery''': ''Recurve Men W2, Recurve Men Standing, Compound Men W1, Compound Men Open, Recurve Women W2, Recurve Women Standing, Compound Women Open, Visually Impaired Open'' * '''Nations''': ''National rankings based on all disciplines''
From 2006, rankings were calculated for [[Field Archery]], but since 2012 are no longer maintained.<ref>http://www.archeryranking.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=652&Itemid=1&lang=en</ref>
==Calculation==
Each archer or team earns a ranking score for each competition. The ranking scores are calculated through a combination of the ranking factor of the tournament ("Ranking Factor") and points based on the competitor's final position in the competition ("Ranking Score"). The archer's four highest ranking scores are then combined to form their total score ("Added Ranking Score"), which forms the basis of the ranking list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archery.org/UserFiles/Document/Results/World%20Ranking/WorldRanking_CalculationSystem.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 10, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228065232/http://www.archery.org/UserFiles/Document/Results/World%20Ranking/WorldRanking_CalculationSystem.pdf |archivedate=December 28, 2013 }}</ref>
===Ranking Factor=== Only results achieved at official ranking events can count towards the overall rankings. These events include the major [[World Archery Federation]] tournaments ([[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]], [[World Archery Championships]], [[FITA Archery World Cup|World Cup]]), and other international, regional and national events that have applied and been approved for ranking status.
The tournament ranking factor is calculated on the basis of three sub-factors, Quality, Quantity and Period, which are multiplied together to produce the overall tournament factor. The factor can vary between disciplines at the same event (e.g., the recurve and compound disciplines at the World Championships may have different Ranking Factors).
For instance, the Ranking Factor of a tournament for individuals with 60 archers, of whom 10 are in the top 50, that took place 18 months ago, would be:
'''2.5''' ''("Quality": 9-12 top 50 archers)'' x
'''0.9''' ''("Quantity": 33-64 archers)'' x
'''0.5''' ''("Period": other tournament 12-24 months ago)'' =
'''''1.125'''''
====Quality==== The Quality sub-factor takes into account the level of competition at the tournament. A score is assigned based on the prestige of the event, for the major [[World Archery Federation]] tournaments, and the number of top archers or teams at other competitions (defined as individuals ranked in the top 50 or teams ranked in the top 16). The quality factor points are assigned as follows:
{{Col-begin}} {{Col-1-of-2}} '''Individual''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:300px;"|Tournament ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:100px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]] || 5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[World Archery Championships]] || 5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[FITA Archery World Cup|World Cup]] ''(excl. World Cup Finals)'' || 4.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with more than 20 top archers || 4 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 17-20 top archers || 3.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 13-16 top archers || 3 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 9-12 top archers || 2.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 5-8 top archers || 2 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 1-4 top archers || 1.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with no top archers || 1 |}
{{Col-2-of-2}} '''Team''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:300px;"|Tournament ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:100px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]] || 5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[World Archery Championships]] || 5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| [[FITA Archery World Cup|World Cup]] ''(excl. World Cup Finals)'' || 4.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with more than 10 top teams || 4 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 9-10 top teams || 3.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 7-8 top teams || 3 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 5-6 top teams || 2.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 3-4 top teams || 2 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with 1-2 top teams || 1.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Competition with no top teams || 1 |} {{Col-end}}
====Quantity==== The Quantity sub-factor assigns a score based on the number of archers competing as follows:
{{Col-begin}} {{Col-1-of-2}} '''Individual''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:400px;"|Number of archers ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:100px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| More than 64 (including [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]]) || 1 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 33-64 || 0.9 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 17-32 || 0.8 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 9-16 || 0.7 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Fewer than 9, with a Quality factor of 1.5 or more ''(ie, with at least 1 top 50 archer)'' || 0.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Fewer than 9, with a Quality factor of 1 ''(ie, with no top 50 archers)'' || 0 |} {{Col-2-of-2}} '''Team''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:400px;"|Number of teams ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:100px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| More than 16 (including [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]]) || 1 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 13-15 || 0.9 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 9-12 || 0.8 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 5-8 || 0.7 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 4 || 0.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| Fewer than 4 || 0 |} {{Col-end}}
====Period==== The Period sub-factor is dependent on when the competition took place, allowing the Ranking Factor to emphasise the most recent tournaments as follows:
{| cellspacing="1" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:250px;"|Tournament ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:250px;"|Period ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:100px;"|Points |- | rowspan=3 valign="top" | [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]] || Up to 12 months after the tournament || 1 |- | 12–24 months after the tournament || 0.8 |- | More than 24 months after the tournament || 0 |- | rowspan=3 valign="top" | [[World Archery Championships]] || Up to 12 months after the tournament || 1 |- | After 12 months until the next tournament || 0.8 |- | After the next tournament || 0 |- | rowspan=3 valign="top" | Continental Championships || Up to 12 months after the tournament || 1 |- | After 12 months until the next tournament || 0.8 |- | After the next tournament || 0 |- | rowspan=3 valign="top" | Other tournaments || Up to 12 months after the tournament || 1 |- | 12–24 months after the tournament || 0.5 |- | More than 24 months after the tournament || 0 |}
===Ranking Points===
Ranking Points are awarded based on the team or competitor's final position at the competition. This is then multiplied by the Ranking Factor to produce the overall Ranking Score for that team or competitor at that tournament. For instance, an archer who finished 4th in the competition used in the example above would receive the following Ranking Score:
'''1.125''' ''("Ranking Factor")'' x
'''12''' ''("Ranking Points": 4th place)'' =
'''''13.5'''''
A team or competitor's best four Ranking Scores are then combined to produce the Added Ranking Score, which forms the basis of the rankings list. No more than two Ranking Scores whose period factor is lower than 1 may be used to calculate the Added Ranking Score.
Ranking Points are awarded as follows:
{{Col-begin}} {{Col-1-of-2}} '''Individual''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:250px;"|Final position ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:150px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| 1 || 20 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 2 || 17 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 3 || 14 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 4 || 12 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 5 || 10 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 6 || 9.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 7 || 9 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 8 || 8.5 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 9-16 ''(i.e., all losing quarter finalists)'' || 7 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 17-32 ''(i.e., all losing 1/8 finalists)'' || 4 |} {{Col-2-of-2}} '''Team''' {| cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" style="border:1px solid #aaa; font-size:90%;" |- style="background:#e4e4e4;" ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:250px;"|Final position ! style="border-bottom:1px solid #aaa; width:150px;"|Number of points |- | style="text-align:center;"| 1 || 25 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 2 || 21 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 3 || 18 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 4 || 15 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 5 || 13 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 6 || 12 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 7 || 11 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 8 || 10 |- | style="text-align:center;"| 9-16 ''(i.e., all losing quarter finalists)'' || 8 |} {{Col-end}}
